Following \citet*{Rockafellar1970} , Chapter 26 , we define the Legendre - Fenchel 's conjugate $C^{*}(\cdot,\mu):\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}\longrightarrow\mathbb{R}$ of the mental cost function $C(\cdot,\mu):\Delta(\Omega)\longrightarrow\mathbb{R}$ as follows :  egin{equation}\label{eqn:convex_conjugate} C^{*}(x,\mu)=\max_{\eta\in\Delta(\Omega)}\langle x,\etaangle-C(\eta,\mu), \end{equation} for all $x\in\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}$ , where $\langle\cdot,\cdotangle$ is the standard inner product on $\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}$ . We know that the function $C^{*}(\cdot,\mu):\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}\longrightarrow\mathbb{R}$ is ( i ) strictly convex ; ( ii ) is differentiable and has gradient given by  egin{equation}\label{eqn:convex_conjugate_gradient} 
abla_{x}C^{*}(x,\mu)=\underset{\eta\in\Delta^{R}_{a}}{\arg\max}\langle x,\etaangle-C(\eta,\mu), \end{equation} for all $x\in\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}$ ; and ( iii ) the gradient $
abla_{x}C^{*}(\cdot,\mu):\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}\longrightarrow\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}$ is a monotone increasing ( invertible ) mapping if , and only if , \cref{as:1} holds \citep[see][Theorem 26.6]{Rockafellar1970} . Moreover , we know that the convex conjugate is defined up to a linear scaling , so for any $	heta>0$ ,  egin{equation}\label{eqn:convex_conjugate_scaling}  rac{1}{	heta} C^{*}\left(	heta x,\muight)=\max_{\eta\in\Delta(\Omega)}\langle x,\etaangle- rac{1}{	heta}C(\eta,\mu), \end{equation} for all $x\in\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}$ . Remarking that $\mathbb{E}_{\eta}u(a,\omega)=\langle u_{a},\etaangle$ and $\mathbb{E}_{\mu}u(a,\omega)=\langle u_{a},\muangle$ we can deduce from \cref{eqn:convex_conjugate,eqn:convex_conjugate_scaling} that  egin{equation}\label{eqn:well_being_closed_form} W_a(\mu)= rac{1}{	heta} C^{*}\left(	heta u_{a},\muight) \end{equation} for any $a\in A$ and $\mu\in\Delta(\Omega)$ . Moreover , using \labelcref{eqn:convex_conjugate_gradient} we get  egin{equation}\label{eqn:distortion_equal_gradient} 
abla_{x}C^{*}(u_{a},\mu)=\eta_a(	heta u_{a},\mu) \end{equation} for any $a\in A$ and $\mu\in\Delta(\Omega)$ . Finally , as $
abla_{x}C^{*}(\cdot,\mu):\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}\longrightarrow\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}$ is a monotone increasing mapping , the function $\eta_a(\cdot,\mu):\mathbb{R}^{|\Omega|}\longrightarrow\Delta(\Omega)$ must be increasing in the payoff vector by \cref{eqn:distortion_equal_gradient} . \end{proof} Finally , we show how distortions in beliefs translate into distortions in behavior . The next proposition formally states that a wishful Receiver behaves as if her utility function was given by her optimal psychological well - being . It comes as a direct corollary of \cref{prop:opt_belief_as1} and subsumes \cref{prop:opt_behavior_KL} .  egin{corollary} [ Receiver 's equilibrium behavior ] \label{prop:receiver_behavior_as1} Assume $C(\eta,\mu)$ satisfies \cref{as:1} . Receiver 's optimal action correspondence is given by  egin{equation*} A(\eta(\mu))=\hat{A}(\mu) \end{equation*} for any $\mu\in\Delta(\Omega)$ where  egin{equation*} \hat{A}(\mu)=\underset{a\in A}{\arg\max} \; W_a(\mu), \end{equation*} for any $\mu\in\Delta(\Omega)$ and any $	heta\in\mathbb{R}_{+}^{*}$ . \end{corollary}

